@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Resources";
}

<div class="resources-page">
    <h2 class="text-center display-4">Welcome to our Resource page</h2>
    <p class="text-center">Here you will find useful links and information about fire safety, food pantries, and evacuation routes in case of a wildfire emergency.</p>

    <div class="accordion mx-auto" id="resourceAccordion" style="max-width: 800px;">
        <!-- Food Pantries -->
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#foodPantries">
                    Food Pantry
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="foodPantries" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#resourceAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <ul>
                        <h5 class ="text-center">In the event of wildfire that results in the loss of access to food we aim to provide a way to help you locate
                            the nearest food pantry. Using the link below you will be directed to Feeding America website, which is the largest charity 
                            "working to end hunger in the United States. We partner with food banks, food pantries, and local food programs to bring food
                            to people facing hunger. We advocate for policies that create long-term solutions to hunger."
                        </h5>
                        <h5 class="text-center"><a href="https://www.feedingamerica.org/find-your-local-foodbank" target="_blank">Feeding America</a></h5>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Fire Safety -->
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#fireSafety">
                    Fire Safety
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="fireSafety" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#resourceAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <h5 class="text-center">Fire safety is critical in preventing fires at home and learning how wildfires can impact your home even
                        though you might be at a "safe distance" from the fire itself. Below is a video that shows how wildfires can burn unsuspecting
                        homes and how one might be able to prevent it. Here you'll find links to the <a href="https://www.redcross.org/get-help/how-to-prepare-for-emergencies/types-of-emergencies/fire.html?srsltid=AfmBOorL2Ekl5KdnF1bg1y4_GmCWyec-7VVWagmdcXcOZTi_j_CfqRCl" 
                        target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">American Red Cross</a> and the <a href="https://www.nfpa.org/education-and-research/wildfire" 
                        target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">National Fire Protection Association</a> that will include further information.
                    </h5>
                    <div class="ratio ratio-16x9">
                        <iframe src="https://youtube.com/embed/3QthynXympI" title="Fire Safety Video" allowfullscreen></iframe>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Evacuation Routes -->
        <div class="accordion-item">
            <h2 class="accordion-header">
                <button class="accordion-button" type="button" data-bs-toggle="collapse" data-bs-target="#evacRoutes">
                    Evacuation Routes
                </button>
            </h2>
            <div id="evacRoutes" class="accordion-collapse collapse" data-bs-parent="#resourceAccordion">
                <div class="accordion-body">
                    <h5 class="text-center">Knowing how and where to evacaute is vital in the event of a wildfire
                        sometimes you may have only minutes to evacuate. Below are links on how to prepare yourself
                        for an evacuation, how to stay vigilant on local alerts, what to bring, and how to plan out
                        an escape route.
                    </h5>
                    <ul>
                        <h5 class="text-center"><a href="https://www.ready.gov/evacuation" target="_blank">Ready.gov</a></h5>
                        <h5 class="text-center"><a href="https://wildfire.oregon.gov/Pages/prepare.aspx" target="_blank">Oregon Widlfire Response & Recovery</a></h5>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>